Program: Discovery
Title: Ionic liquids
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p03jryvn
Last Broadcast Date: 21 December 2004
A look at the potential of ionic liquids. Ionic liquids can turn us into environmentally-friendly chemists: they are liquids containing charged atoms or molecules which act as a universal solvent as well as a chemical reactor. Presenter: Peter Evans. Producer: Helen Sharp.